1
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:09,190
♪

2
00:00:09,190 --> 00:00:11,190
(singing in Japanese)

3
00:00:11,190 --> 00:01:44,260
♪

4
00:01:48,020 --> 00:01:52,090
♪

5
00:01:52,090 --> 00:01:55,270
Kaishu Katsu, we are holding
your daughter Itsuko captive.

6
00:01:55,270 --> 00:01:58,100
At the moment, we have no
intention of harming her,

7
00:01:58,100 --> 00:02:02,010
but that may change depending
on your response to this letter.

8
00:02:02,010 --> 00:02:06,080
If you don't do as we ask, we
may have to take drastic action.

9
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:07,180
We want the money you hid away

10
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:09,210
just before the
fall of Castle Edo.

11
00:02:09,210 --> 00:02:12,030
And we want you to
deliver it personally.

12
00:02:12,030 --> 00:02:14,150
Signed: Beni Aoi.

13
00:02:14,150 --> 00:02:30,150
♪

14
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,140
Huh?

15
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:46,100
Any luck?

16
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:48,150
Did you find Itsuko?

17
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:50,110
She's disappeared completely.

18
00:02:50,110 --> 00:02:53,130
Without a trace, we've checked
everywhere in the neighborhood.

19
00:02:53,130 --> 00:02:55,190
Huh?

20
00:02:55,190 --> 00:02:56,140
Daigoro!

21
00:02:56,140 --> 00:02:59,130
(panting)

22
00:02:59,130 --> 00:03:02,050
She's not down at
the produce shop.

23
00:03:02,050 --> 00:03:04,200
I'm worried, I can't
imagine where she went.

24
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:07,210
Something really awful must have
happened to her, I can sense it.

25
00:03:07,210 --> 00:03:09,080
Calm down just a minute.

26
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:11,190
For all we know, she
went home to her father's.

27
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:13,080
If that's true, it would
have been nice of her

28
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,210
to tell us where
she was going.

29
00:03:14,210 --> 00:03:16,190
(groans)

30
00:03:16,190 --> 00:03:19,140
I will give it one more try.

31
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:21,100
Wait a minute, you
can't just run off

32
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:23,090
when you don't have the first
idea what happened to her.

33
00:03:23,090 --> 00:03:24,110
Take it easy!

34
00:03:24,110 --> 00:03:26,090
Listen, she could
be in big trouble!

35
00:03:26,090 --> 00:03:27,010
Where's Kenshin?

36
00:03:27,010 --> 00:03:28,110
He'll know what to do.

37
00:03:28,110 --> 00:03:30,170
I'm afraid he hasn't
made it back yet.

38
00:03:30,170 --> 00:03:33,050
Now I'm getting worried
about what's happened to him.

39
00:03:40,230 --> 00:03:42,200
(clock ticking)

40
00:03:49,140 --> 00:03:51,110
(ticking echoes)

41
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:56,240
(beating drums)

42
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:11,040
We should fight.

43
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:13,160
That's suicide,
we should negotiate.

44
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:16,150
It's too late for that,
the army is closing in on us.

45
00:04:16,150 --> 00:04:19,130
We still have options, why
don't we ask France for help?

46
00:04:19,130 --> 00:04:20,170
And have them take over?

47
00:04:20,170 --> 00:04:22,130
That's a stupid suggestion.

48
00:04:22,130 --> 00:04:24,020
Are you calling me stupid?

49
00:04:24,020 --> 00:04:26,010
Watch your tongue,
before I rip it out!

50
00:04:26,010 --> 00:04:28,190
One more word and you won't
have to face the Satsuma army,

51
00:04:28,190 --> 00:04:30,130
because I'll kill you myself!

52
00:04:30,130 --> 00:04:32,060
Stop all this senseless arguing,

53
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:34,060
it's not going to
solve the problem!

54
00:04:34,060 --> 00:04:36,160
We need to come up with a
plan to marshal our forces

55
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:38,130
and neutralize
the army's advance!

56
00:04:38,130 --> 00:04:39,130
(clicking)

57
00:04:39,130 --> 00:04:42,260
♪

58
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:43,270
Katsu.

59
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:45,110
Yes, my Lord?

60
00:04:45,110 --> 00:04:48,030
♪

61
00:04:48,030 --> 00:04:51,130
What's the situation
in the city of Edo?

62
00:04:51,130 --> 00:04:53,220
There's a general atmosphere
of fear and panic since

63
00:04:53,220 --> 00:04:55,150
the population heard
the news last night

64
00:04:55,150 --> 00:04:57,290
that the Satsuma
army is closing in.

65
00:04:57,290 --> 00:05:00,250
The streets are filled with
people determined to evacuate.

66
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:03,090
So many loyalists are
trying to escape in boats,

67
00:05:03,090 --> 00:05:04,180
all order has broken down,

68
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:07,250
and the dock area
is in total chaos.

69
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:09,140
It's worse than I thought.

70
00:05:09,140 --> 00:05:10,120
Thank you, Katsu.

71
00:05:12,180 --> 00:05:16,180
The Tokugawa era, the world
we knew, is about to end.

72
00:05:16,180 --> 00:05:18,110
That is reality.

73
00:05:18,110 --> 00:05:20,030
We are outnumbered
by our opponents,

74
00:05:20,030 --> 00:05:22,190
and further resistance
would be futile.

75
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:25,100
I cannot cause more
bloodshed for Edo.

76
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:28,030
I have failed my people.

77
00:05:28,030 --> 00:05:29,170
Not so, my Lord!

78
00:05:29,170 --> 00:05:31,050
I must end this conflict,

79
00:05:31,050 --> 00:05:34,290
even at the risk
of my own life.

80
00:05:34,290 --> 00:05:37,120
Sire.

81
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:40,150
I am overwhelmed by
your commitment, Shogun.

82
00:05:40,150 --> 00:05:41,290
I will do everything in my power

83
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:45,270
to help you carry out this
last noble act of leadership.

84
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:47,110
Thank you, Katsu.

85
00:05:47,110 --> 00:05:50,210
♪

86
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:52,210
(crickets chirring)

87
00:05:52,210 --> 00:06:07,280
♪

88
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:09,200
Mr. Katsu?

89
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:12,020
Yeh?

90
00:06:12,020 --> 00:06:13,120
Mr. Himura.

91
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:23,170
♪

92
00:06:23,170 --> 00:06:25,010
"We'll expect you
at 2:00 A.M.

93
00:06:25,010 --> 00:06:27,160
at the Ryougen
temple in Shinagawa."

94
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,110
Beni Aoi.

95
00:06:29,110 --> 00:06:31,100
I'm very sorry, Mr. Katsu.

96
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:33,210
I guess I didn't
take them seriously.

97
00:06:33,210 --> 00:06:34,270
Don't blame yourself,

98
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:36,280
I didn't take them
seriously, either,

99
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:39,030
but I am puzzled.

100
00:06:39,030 --> 00:06:41,060
How did these men
know about the money?

101
00:06:41,060 --> 00:06:42,210
As far as the
government knows,

102
00:06:42,210 --> 00:06:44,170
after the war,
it disappeared.

103
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:47,050
You mean you do have money
hidden away somewhere?

104
00:06:47,050 --> 00:06:49,110
Quite a bit.

105
00:06:49,110 --> 00:06:51,280
I trust you, and I'm willing
to tell you the truth,

106
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:53,240
but no one else
knows about this,

107
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:56,080
including my pupils
and my daughter Itsuko,

108
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,160
and no one must ever know.

109
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:02,030
♪

110
00:07:02,030 --> 00:07:04,070
This money represents
the personal fortune

111
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:05,180
of the shogun.

112
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:07,050
He gave it to me himself.

113
00:07:07,050 --> 00:07:08,130
The last shogun?

114
00:07:08,130 --> 00:07:09,280
Yoshinobu Tokugawa?

115
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:11,050
Yes, my boy.

116
00:07:11,050 --> 00:07:13,110
We were always
told it was stolen.

117
00:07:13,110 --> 00:07:14,220
Course you were.

118
00:07:14,220 --> 00:07:17,080
Just imagine what would
have happened otherwise.

119
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:19,000
Master Yoshinobu would
have been tortured

120
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,270
until he told the army
commanders where it was.

121
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:24,270
So we put out a false story
about thieves breaking in

122
00:07:24,270 --> 00:07:27,020
during the chaos,
and I hid it away.

123
00:07:29,150 --> 00:07:31,100
Events moved
quickly in those days,

124
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:33,270
and people's
loyalties were suspect.

125
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:35,250
But the shogun knew
I could be trusted,

126
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:37,250
and I've never
betrayed him since.

127
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:41,200
I've been waiting
for the right moment

128
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:43,090
to put that money to use.

129
00:07:43,090 --> 00:07:47,020
♪

130
00:07:47,020 --> 00:07:50,200
It's been 10 years since
Master Yoshinobu voluntarily

131
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:53,010
abdicated his
position as shogun.

132
00:07:53,010 --> 00:08:01,140
♪

133
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:03,280
All during that time,
he's been a prisoner,

134
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:08,050
kept under house arrest
by the Meiji government.

135
00:08:08,050 --> 00:08:11,080
They're still afraid of
the power his name carries,

136
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:14,130
and they've made sure
he has no base of support.

137
00:08:14,130 --> 00:08:16,100
And they're right to
fear his influence.

138
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,200
There are many
who would join him

139
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:20,050
if he were allowed
to reclaim his position.

140
00:08:20,050 --> 00:08:21,140
I want to use that money

141
00:08:21,140 --> 00:08:24,040
to make sure he
is safely released.

142
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:27,010
The remainder, I'll give back
to him to use as he wishes.

143
00:08:27,010 --> 00:08:29,180
My final act of loyalty.

144
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:30,220
I understand.

145
00:08:30,220 --> 00:08:34,200
♪

146
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:36,100
Why don't you let
me come with you?

147
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:38,150
I might be able to help.

148
00:08:38,150 --> 00:08:41,000
I have to do this alone.

149
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,060
They have taken my
daughter hostage.

150
00:08:43,060 --> 00:08:47,000
Simple honor requires that I be
the one to go in and rescue her.

151
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,000
I thank you for
the offer though.

152
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,150
I can see from your sword
that what it represents,

153
00:08:51,150 --> 00:08:53,220
that you would be
a formidable ally.

154
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:56,000
I made a vow to never
again be the instrument

155
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,140
of another person's death,

156
00:08:57,140 --> 00:08:59,090
and I've been
true to my oath.

157
00:08:59,090 --> 00:09:01,100
I respect your
refusal to do the same,

158
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:03,290
although I imagine
the temptation is great.

159
00:09:03,290 --> 00:09:06,140
Overwhelming, but
I'm a stubborn old man.

160
00:09:06,140 --> 00:09:10,010
♪

161
00:09:10,010 --> 00:09:12,280
Better go, just
a few hours left.

162
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:14,220
Do you have
a plan in mind?

163
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,270
(laughs)

164
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:17,230
The broad strokes
aren't formulated yet,

165
00:09:17,230 --> 00:09:19,110
much less the details.

166
00:09:19,110 --> 00:09:20,270
But it won't involve
giving them the money

167
00:09:20,270 --> 00:09:23,170
or allowing them to
kill me or my daughter.

168
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:26,060
That doesn't leave much room
for negotiation, does it?

169
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:28,030
Not really.

170
00:09:28,030 --> 00:09:30,240
By the way, please don't
say anything to Daigoro.

171
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:33,070
He's not a brave boy,
but he's very emotional,

172
00:09:33,070 --> 00:09:35,100
and he might decide
to do something rash.

173
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:36,280
I'm not sure how
this will end,

174
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:38,090
and I don't want
him to get hurt.

175
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:42,010
Goodbye.

176
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,200
Hey, Kenshin.

177
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,270
The Kamiya dojo is
the other direction.

178
00:09:52,270 --> 00:09:54,290
You're right,
I was dreaming.

179
00:09:54,290 --> 00:09:57,040
Kenshin, I really wish you'd
taken the time to tell us

180
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:58,150
you were coming over here.

181
00:09:58,150 --> 00:09:59,230
We were very worried!

182
00:09:59,230 --> 00:10:01,240
Was Miss Itsuko at
home with her father?

183
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:04,210
We haven't been able to find
her anywhere, is she all right?

184
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:09,180
Why aren't you answering me?

185
00:10:09,180 --> 00:10:12,100
Something bad has happened
to Miss Itsuko, hasn't it?

186
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:15,010
But Daigoro,
I can explain it,

187
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:16,110
but we can't talk here.

188
00:10:16,110 --> 00:10:18,130
Come with me, let's
go sit down somewhere.

189
00:10:24,070 --> 00:10:30,000
♪

190
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:30,392
Seriously?

191
00:10:30,392 --> 00:10:32,100
She was kidnapped?

192
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:33,060
Why abduct her?

193
00:10:33,060 --> 00:10:35,090
Her father has no money.

194
00:10:35,090 --> 00:10:37,280
♪

195
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,230
Come on, would you get
a hold of yourself?

196
00:10:39,230 --> 00:10:40,280
This doesn't look good.

197
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,160
I know, I'm just weak.

198
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:44,160
Well, you could try
a little harder.

199
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:47,160
The truth is, Mr. Katsu asked me
not to tell you what occurred.

200
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:49,150
Still, I thought
you ought to know.

201
00:10:49,150 --> 00:10:52,030
He figures I'm powerless
to do anything about it.

202
00:10:52,030 --> 00:10:53,200
I don't think so, Daigoro.

203
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,090
He seemed more concerned
about what could happen

204
00:10:55,090 --> 00:10:57,190
if you tried to do something.

205
00:10:57,190 --> 00:10:59,180
Kenshin, we have to
help get Itsuko back

206
00:10:59,180 --> 00:11:01,050
before something bad happens.

207
00:11:01,050 --> 00:11:02,210
I think we should
go tell the police.

208
00:11:02,210 --> 00:11:06,070
Well, if you want my opinion,
I think that's a bad idea.

209
00:11:06,070 --> 00:11:07,030
How so?

210
00:11:07,030 --> 00:11:08,180
The police train
for matters like this.

211
00:11:08,180 --> 00:11:09,280
Yes, but they're
not impartial.

212
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:12,110
They've been keeping
an eye on Mr. Katsu.

213
00:11:12,110 --> 00:11:14,250
If they think he's been
hiding the Tokugawa money,

214
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:17,000
they'll come in
and arrest him.

215
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,090
I think that is the single
reason he is determined

216
00:11:19,090 --> 00:11:21,020
to handle this
problem by himself.

217
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:22,100
No one's going with him?

218
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:25,060
Come on, that's suicide!

219
00:11:25,060 --> 00:11:26,140
He's willing
to take that risk,

220
00:11:26,140 --> 00:11:28,060
and it's not our
place to interfere.

221
00:11:28,060 --> 00:11:29,210
For all we know,
he could pull it off.

222
00:11:29,210 --> 00:11:31,080
Or be killed!

223
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,150
Gotta think!

224
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:34,260
Hey wait, we
still have Tatsuma

225
00:11:34,260 --> 00:11:36,040
if the police are no good.

226
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:38,000
Yes, but can he be trusted?

227
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,290
He's working for
the Meiji government.

228
00:11:39,290 --> 00:11:42,050
The politicians are
worse than the police.

229
00:11:42,050 --> 00:11:44,210
No, he's been protecting
Mr. Katsu from the government.

230
00:11:44,210 --> 00:11:46,010
He's loyal to the family,

231
00:11:46,010 --> 00:11:47,270
he'll do whatever it
takes to help them.

232
00:11:47,270 --> 00:11:49,230
Believe me, I know he will!

233
00:11:49,230 --> 00:12:09,180
♪

234
00:12:09,180 --> 00:12:12,200
It will all be
over by sunrise.

235
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:18,110
Trust me, Tatsuma can take
care of this problem without

236
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:20,280
tipping things off
to the government.

237
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:24,050
Ugh, I really don't like the
idea of owing a politician

238
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:25,160
a favor in return.

239
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:27,230
At this stage, what
other options do we have?

240
00:12:27,230 --> 00:12:29,020
Are you all right with this?

241
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:30,090
What?

242
00:12:30,090 --> 00:12:31,250
How do you feel
about stepping aside

243
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,260
and letting somebody else go
in and save Itsuko's life?

244
00:12:34,260 --> 00:12:36,000
Well, I...

245
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:41,240
♪

246
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:43,190
If we want to reach
Shinagawa by 2:00 AM,

247
00:12:43,190 --> 00:12:47,010
we're gonna have to
leave pretty soon.

248
00:12:47,010 --> 00:12:49,030
What do you think, Kenshin?

249
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:51,190
Mr. Katsu said for me
to not get involved.

250
00:12:51,190 --> 00:12:53,060
But you've always had
a hearing problem when

251
00:12:53,060 --> 00:12:56,250
it comes to helping
out the underdog.

252
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:59,180
Oh, well, I guess I'm ready
to be scolded by Mr. Katsu

253
00:12:59,180 --> 00:13:01,210
for interfering
in his business.

254
00:13:01,210 --> 00:13:03,210
I thought you'd feel that way.

255
00:13:03,210 --> 00:13:06,150
Well, you're not going
alone, we're coming too!

256
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:08,170
I don't suppose I can
talk you out of this.

257
00:13:08,170 --> 00:13:10,160
Don't even think about it!

258
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:13,070
Wait for us at the dojo,
I'm not gonna miss the fun.

259
00:13:13,070 --> 00:13:14,260
Anyway, I owe this to Itsuko,

260
00:13:14,260 --> 00:13:16,240
she cooked a good meal
for me last week.

261
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:18,280
You think dry rice
is a good meal.

262
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:19,290
Aw, what do you know?

263
00:13:19,290 --> 00:13:21,190
You can't even boil water!

264
00:13:21,190 --> 00:13:22,200
Yes I can!

265
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,210
Wait!

266
00:13:24,210 --> 00:13:25,280
I want to...

267
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,050
I want to go with you.

268
00:13:27,050 --> 00:13:28,170
You should give this
some more thought,

269
00:13:28,170 --> 00:13:30,020
I'm not sure
you can handle it,

270
00:13:30,020 --> 00:13:33,130
especially if it turns
out we have to fight.

271
00:13:33,130 --> 00:13:35,100
I'm gonna be all
right, don't worry!

272
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:37,240
I want to make sure my
friends get home safely.

273
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:39,200
That's very brave.

274
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,260
Look, I know I don't have
the power of a politician

275
00:13:41,260 --> 00:13:43,180
or the sword skills
of any of you,

276
00:13:43,180 --> 00:13:45,250
but I can't let someone else
fight my battles for me.

277
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:47,060
It's just wrong!

278
00:13:47,060 --> 00:13:48,250
It's a matter of honor.

279
00:13:48,250 --> 00:13:50,280
I'm ashamed of
the way I reacted.

280
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:52,120
A friend of mine
is in great danger,

281
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:54,090
and I don't think about
rescuing her myself,

282
00:13:54,090 --> 00:13:58,120
I think about getting
someone else to do it.

283
00:13:58,120 --> 00:14:00,220
I can see why you wouldn't
want me to come along with you.

284
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:04,230
♪

285
00:14:04,230 --> 00:14:07,220
We mistakenly assumed we
were doing this to protect you.

286
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:10,110
We were wrong, we should
have given you more credit.

287
00:14:10,110 --> 00:14:12,200
You just demonstrated
how brave you are.

288
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,130
Please come with us.

289
00:14:14,130 --> 00:14:16,100
Thank you, Kaoru.

290
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:17,290
Yeah, let's go!

291
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:21,080
We'll rescue Itsuko together!

292
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,280
Yes!

293
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:24,160
Well, then, there's
no time to waste.

294
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,210
Kenshin, you wait here,

295
00:14:25,210 --> 00:14:27,010
I'm going to go to the dojo

296
00:14:27,010 --> 00:14:28,220
to change clothes and
pick up some weapons,

297
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:30,020
I'll be right back!

298
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:32,020
Hey, I need some stuff
too, come with me Daigoro!

299
00:14:32,020 --> 00:14:33,130
I'm right behind you!

300
00:14:33,290 --> 00:14:38,040
♪

301
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:41,030
Come on, Satsuma, let your
hair down a little bit.

302
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:43,030
Why don't you have
a drink and relax?

303
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:46,180
Thank you, I think I will.

304
00:14:46,180 --> 00:14:48,050
There you go,
it's strong stuff,

305
00:14:48,050 --> 00:14:49,210
but it looks like
you can handle it.

306
00:14:49,210 --> 00:14:52,060
By the way, how is
Mr. Katsu doing?

307
00:14:52,060 --> 00:14:53,240
He is doing very well.

308
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,070
That's good,

309
00:14:55,070 --> 00:14:57,220
I imagine the recent incident
regarding the military fund

310
00:14:57,220 --> 00:15:00,110
for Saigo must have been
very upsetting for him.

311
00:15:00,110 --> 00:15:02,230
I know you were
pretty shaken up by it.

312
00:15:02,230 --> 00:15:04,100
You're right about that.

313
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:07,070
By the way, thanks so much
for helping us out that time.

314
00:15:07,070 --> 00:15:09,010
You don't have to
thank me, my boy,

315
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:11,000
it was a pleasure
to be of assistance.

316
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,220
I was convinced it was
nothing but a big mistake.

317
00:15:13,220 --> 00:15:15,280
Mr. Katsu is
a very wise man,

318
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:18,050
and here you were,
studying under him.

319
00:15:18,050 --> 00:15:21,130
You must have gotten quite
an education, you lucky dog.

320
00:15:21,130 --> 00:15:22,290
Yes.

321
00:15:22,290 --> 00:15:24,030
I'm glad to see you've become

322
00:15:24,030 --> 00:15:26,020
a student of
governmental procedure.

323
00:15:26,020 --> 00:15:28,160
We need more young bucks like
yourself to give the system

324
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:31,160
an overhaul, and bring
us into the modern age.

325
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:32,170
I have great
expectations

326
00:15:32,170 --> 00:15:33,230
for you, my boy.

327
00:15:33,230 --> 00:15:35,170
That's kind of you,
I plan to work very hard

328
00:15:35,170 --> 00:15:37,250
to meet those expectations.

329
00:15:37,250 --> 00:15:39,070
I believe you will.

330
00:15:39,070 --> 00:15:42,140
I want you to meet some people
who would be very helpful.

331
00:15:42,140 --> 00:15:44,080
I think we should put
you on the fast track

332
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,170
as soon as possible.

333
00:15:45,170 --> 00:15:46,290
Can I quote you on that?

334
00:15:46,290 --> 00:15:48,290
Officially?

335
00:15:48,290 --> 00:15:50,100
I can see you're
already learning

336
00:15:50,100 --> 00:15:51,280
to swim with the sharks.

337
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:52,220
That's good.

338
00:15:52,220 --> 00:15:55,000
It shows you're not a fool.

339
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:59,230
♪

340
00:15:59,230 --> 00:16:00,260
Innkeeper!

341
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:02,280
Bring more sake
for my friend, here.

342
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:04,010
♪

343
00:16:07,030 --> 00:16:09,070
Daigoro, Daigoro!

344
00:16:09,070 --> 00:16:15,160
♪

345
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:18,040
Oh, Daigoro, sleeping
on the job again.

346
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:19,190
♪

347
00:16:19,190 --> 00:16:23,080
I see you haven't
gotten very far.

348
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:25,140
Don't be too hard on him Itsuko,

349
00:16:25,140 --> 00:16:27,090
he was studying
pretty late last night.

350
00:16:27,090 --> 00:16:28,230
Tatsuma!

351
00:16:28,230 --> 00:16:30,110
Good morning, Itsuko.

352
00:16:30,110 --> 00:16:33,050
It's good to see that Daigoro is
applying himself to his studies,

353
00:16:33,050 --> 00:16:35,240
but he's taking a long time
to get with the program.

354
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:38,070
I hope he'll be a credit
to the sensei someday.

355
00:16:38,070 --> 00:16:39,200
I'm certain he will.

356
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:42,170
With time, he will mature and
he will take his place here.

357
00:16:42,170 --> 00:16:45,210
But I must admit, I am
enjoying his exuberance.

358
00:16:45,210 --> 00:16:48,190
The best thing about this era
is that young people are free

359
00:16:48,190 --> 00:16:50,250
to live their lives to
pursue their own happiness

360
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:52,140
without interference.

361
00:16:52,140 --> 00:16:54,110
And even if I'm
not here to see it,

362
00:16:54,110 --> 00:16:57,020
that's a very good sign for
the future of our country.

363
00:16:57,020 --> 00:16:58,190
Hearing you speak
like that, Father,

364
00:16:58,190 --> 00:17:00,240
you'd think you were
about to pass away.

365
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:03,000
The truth is, you're in
the prime of your life.

366
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,140
You're active and vigorous!

367
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:06,050
She's right, you know.

368
00:17:06,050 --> 00:17:08,080
Now, don't you
two worry about me,

369
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:10,250
I plan to live for
a good long time.

370
00:17:15,210 --> 00:17:16,230
Daigoro?

371
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:18,230
I see you're awake.

372
00:17:18,230 --> 00:17:19,250
Who are you?

373
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:21,060
And where are we?

374
00:17:21,060 --> 00:17:22,270
I am the leader
of the Beni Aoi,

375
00:17:22,270 --> 00:17:24,170
a group you're
not familiar with,

376
00:17:24,170 --> 00:17:27,010
and this is
a temple in Shinagawa.

377
00:17:27,010 --> 00:17:28,150
Why did you bring me here?

378
00:17:28,150 --> 00:17:30,120
What do you want with me?

379
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:31,210
(whimpers)

380
00:17:31,210 --> 00:17:33,200
We have no intention
of harming you,

381
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,070
as long as you
don't try to escape,

382
00:17:35,070 --> 00:17:36,280
you will not be tied up.

383
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:38,160
Once you've served
your purpose,

384
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,280
you will be released.

385
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:41,240
What purpose is that?

386
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:43,160
To bring your father...

387
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:44,270
Kaishu Katsu.

388
00:17:44,270 --> 00:17:47,060
Why are you trying to
bring my father here?

389
00:17:47,060 --> 00:17:48,110
To kill him.

390
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:49,140
Why?

391
00:17:49,140 --> 00:17:54,200
♪

392
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:57,190
All the people here used
to be vassals of the shogun,

393
00:17:57,190 --> 00:18:00,030
proud warriors,
masters of the land,

394
00:18:00,030 --> 00:18:02,180
now reduced to pitiful beggars.

395
00:18:02,180 --> 00:18:06,000
Without hope, we simply
exist, waiting to die.

396
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,230
It's the Meiji legacy.

397
00:18:07,230 --> 00:18:10,100
♪

398
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:12,010
They took away
everything we had

399
00:18:12,010 --> 00:18:14,190
and threw our families
into the street.

400
00:18:14,190 --> 00:18:19,060
♪

401
00:18:19,060 --> 00:18:21,280
We were exiled to the
most desolate outposts,

402
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:24,260
and our family members either
escaped to other countries,

403
00:18:24,260 --> 00:18:26,170
or died in despair.

404
00:18:26,170 --> 00:18:43,250
♪

405
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:46,150
We all knew who was
responsible for our adversity,

406
00:18:46,150 --> 00:18:48,040
and we swore revenge.

407
00:18:48,040 --> 00:19:01,010
♪

408
00:19:01,010 --> 00:19:03,030
One man, more than any other,

409
00:19:03,030 --> 00:19:07,060
talked the shogun into
giving up without a fight.

410
00:19:07,060 --> 00:19:08,290
He forced us to surrender.

411
00:19:08,290 --> 00:19:10,170
Are you blaming my father?

412
00:19:10,170 --> 00:19:11,180
How can you?

413
00:19:11,180 --> 00:19:13,110
The man was
trying to save them!

414
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:16,180
He knew the army was
going to kill everyone!

415
00:19:16,180 --> 00:19:18,210
Your father
accomplished his goal.

416
00:19:18,210 --> 00:19:20,190
We followed the order
because we were told

417
00:19:20,190 --> 00:19:22,140
that this was what
the shogun wanted.

418
00:19:22,140 --> 00:19:24,130
As a result, Edo was saved.

419
00:19:24,130 --> 00:19:26,100
Then why are
you doing this?

420
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:28,140
Because we found out
later that this was not

421
00:19:28,140 --> 00:19:30,110
what the shogun had wanted.

422
00:19:30,110 --> 00:19:31,150
What?

423
00:19:31,150 --> 00:19:33,070
We were able to
discover the truth,

424
00:19:33,070 --> 00:19:35,140
that Katsu misled
us out of greed!

425
00:19:35,140 --> 00:19:37,010
In order to save his own life

426
00:19:37,010 --> 00:19:39,190
and gain control over
the Tokugawa fortune,

427
00:19:39,190 --> 00:19:43,160
he lied to master Yoshinobu
and convinced him to surrender.

428
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:46,040
That's a filthy lie,
you have no proof!

429
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:49,170
Then why does Katsu control a
secret stash of Tokugawa money?

430
00:19:49,170 --> 00:19:50,240
Huh?

431
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:52,200
The Meiji government
is about to move in

432
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:55,020
and find the cash
and confiscate it.

433
00:19:55,020 --> 00:19:56,120
Oh my God.

434
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:58,010
There's no choice now.

435
00:19:58,010 --> 00:20:00,060
For our honor and for
the future of our movement,

436
00:20:00,060 --> 00:20:02,030
Kaishu Katsu has to be killed.

437
00:20:02,030 --> 00:20:04,100
And what will you
accomplish by doing that?

438
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:07,210
We'll be able to reverse
the Meiji restoration.

439
00:20:07,210 --> 00:20:10,040
Killing my father will
topple the government?

440
00:20:12,010 --> 00:20:15,000
Before he dies, he will
turn over the Tokugawa fortune

441
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,160
and we will use that money
to start a revolution.

442
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:21,060
♪

443
00:20:21,060 --> 00:20:23,230
We will put our
master back in power.

444
00:20:23,230 --> 00:20:26,210
Then we will take
revenge on our oppressors!

445
00:20:26,210 --> 00:20:29,110
♪

446
00:20:29,110 --> 00:20:32,060
That is the ultimate
goal of the Beni Aoi.

447
00:20:35,060 --> 00:20:37,190
Your father should
arrive here very soon.

448
00:20:41,240 --> 00:21:23,260
♪

449
00:21:23,260 --> 00:21:24,290
What do you think?

450
00:21:24,290 --> 00:21:26,190
How about launching
a surprise attack?

451
00:21:26,190 --> 00:21:27,290
Are you crazy?

452
00:21:27,290 --> 00:21:29,110
How about finding out how
many people are in there,

453
00:21:29,110 --> 00:21:30,100
first of all?

454
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:31,260
Worried you can't handle it?

455
00:21:31,260 --> 00:21:33,060
I can handle you!

456
00:21:33,060 --> 00:21:35,130
Quiet you nincompoops,
you're gonna give us away!

457
00:21:35,130 --> 00:21:37,090
You know, I don't see
Mr. Katsu anywhere.

458
00:21:37,090 --> 00:21:38,230
First thing we should find out

459
00:21:38,230 --> 00:21:40,260
is what part of he shrine
they're keeping Itsuko in,

460
00:21:40,260 --> 00:21:43,050
and how many men we're facing.

461
00:21:43,050 --> 00:21:45,210
♪

462
00:21:45,210 --> 00:21:48,160
I can do this.

463
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:49,250
Calm down, now.

464
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:52,110
When things get
going, you'll be fine.

465
00:21:52,110 --> 00:21:53,180
Okay.

466
00:21:53,180 --> 00:22:06,230
♪

467
00:22:06,230 --> 00:22:09,040
(shrieks)

468
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:10,110
Daigoro, don't!

469
00:22:10,110 --> 00:22:11,090
(yelling)

470
00:22:11,090 --> 00:22:13,280
Don't touch her!

471
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:14,230
Daigoro, come back!

472
00:22:14,230 --> 00:22:16,030
Leave her alone, you brute!

473
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:18,050
Daigoro!

474
00:22:18,050 --> 00:22:19,180
Stay balanced!

475
00:22:19,180 --> 00:22:20,280
(screaming)

476
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:22,120
(groans)

477
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:24,120
♪

478
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:26,060
(shrieks)

479
00:22:26,060 --> 00:22:32,040
♪

480
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:33,070
No, you cowards!

481
00:22:33,070 --> 00:22:34,160
Daigoro, no!

482
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:44,020
♪

483
00:22:44,020 --> 00:22:45,200
Daigoro!

484
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:47,060
♪

485
00:22:50,030 --> 00:22:56,040
♪

486
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:58,040
(singing in Japanese)

487
00:22:58,040 --> 00:25:12,230
♪

488
00:25:13,260 --> 00:25:16,150
♪

